data.title: Best Quick Grab Salad
data.text: Their Cranberry Walnut salad is a great value. Lots of toppings and can add chicken for a large entree salad at a very reasonable price.

data.title: Who would have thought to find Australian in Georgia
data.text: Pie crust is good, I had a mince tart. It was not what I expected, it was like brownie mixed with mincemeat. Love them in the UK, so maybe this is the Aussie way.

data.title: Fish & Chips From Australian Chef
data.text: Excellent food and cozy unique café.  This was the first stop for us on a food tour around Marietta square.  I don't eat fish, but tried the fish and chips as it was part of the food tour experience and found them to be wonderful.  Completely recommend trying this spot out when you are on the "square" and looking for something to try.  They feature meat pies and those looked yummy too.  Hoping to get back there to try out more tasty treats!

data.title: Great place to Go.
data.text: Love this place, it is clean, food from bread to all the quiches taste so good. Go and try it. You will go back.

data.title: Just LOVE their meat pies...
data.text: Was turned on to this place by some friends who are from Australia. I went to Australia in 2000 and fell in love with meat pies.  Fast forward about 10 years and I find out about this place. I come in and try their meat pies and they are exactly as I remembered them in Australia.  I even buy some and freeze this at home. I just get the standard meat pie with brown gravy.  Even their bakery items are good.  And if you are dying for some Vegi-Mite, they have it there too.

data.title: Good lunch mate!!
data.text: My friends and I were in Marietta Square to go to the Saturday farmers market when we saw this bakery that we had heard about previously. We had to try it!! I got the sausage roll and the shepherds pie and both were very good they could've benefited from a little bit more moisture on for haps sauce to go with them but they were both very tasty and the pastry light and flaky. It was great to see you stop at so many imported items from overseas but of course they were expensive as a result.

data.title: Tasty and authentic
data.text: My teen son' s favorite! Always half full of Aussies, New Zealande, and South Africans looking for a taste of home

data.title: It is just ok!
data.text: Food is not bad, but the place is too small and old. Wasn't too impressed with the workers. I don't think I will go back.

data.title: Awesome food and friendly service
data.text: I love this place. The sandwiches and salad are wonderful. My favorite is their fish & chips. Very good fish with hand cut chips. If your really hungry order the two piece.

data.title: Checked this off my bucket list.
data.text: I had ordered items shipped to the house before and had been wanting to go for awhile. We got there during breakfast time..the young lady said it would be alright to order lunch. My wife and enjoyed every bite. Staff is very friendly and the meat pies are awesome.

data.title: Great food and atmosphere!
data.text: Can't see how anyone can give this a one star. The food was great and is close to authentic as you can get to actually being in Australia. If you want to have a taste of some of the food we like and eat here in Australia, check it out. And whike you are there, by a jar of vegemite!

data.title: Delicious and different
data.text: We don't know how authentic it is, but we think this is probably pretty authentic (and delicious) Australian food.  From pastries to sandwiches to meat pies, we have never been disappointed.

data.title: Excellent Bakery
data.text: This is a great bakery and have lots of authentic Australian style savoury pies. I am a sucker for a good pie so I try to visit this shop when I am in Marietta.

data.title: Yum
data.text: I've been in for lunch many times! It's always good! Albeit a bit unusual vs American flavor so...but interesting & good!

data.title: Welcome Mate!!!!!
data.text: Went there to have lunch on a sunday afternoon.The place  was packet and we got the last availalable table.  we had he shepherds pie and the outback chicken pepperjack pie.  They were very good.

data.title: Wow
data.text: I met a colleague here for a business lunch and was really impressed. The lunch was great, the desserts were amazing! My only issue was the restaurant is not air-conditioned, and the icemaker on the soda machine was not working.

data.title: Awesome Bakery!!!  Everything they make is delicious!!!
data.text: I have several friends that travel quite a bit away to visit Australian Bakery, some from England too and they say the sausage meat pie is amazing as well as everything else!!!

data.title: Awesome for pies and Aussie desserts!
data.text: I crave the food from this place.  The pies (think savory pies for those unfamiliar with Aussie pie---like a meat or chicken pie) are incredible; there is no place I have found in the States to get better pies.  And, the desserts are incredible!  INCREDIBLE.  I haven't stopped in for a bit, but I will guarantee they make a lamination every day, and they are to die for.  Plus, they sell Aussie foods to take home.

data.title: Meat pies
data.text: This place is about as close to Australia you can get without traveling across the world.  The prices are reasonable and food is full of taste.  There is also a lot of products that are sold in Australia.  There is limited seating inside but it's a good idea to seat outside on a nice day.  Definitely adding this to the list of favorites.

data.title: Best place to go for an Aussie pie
data.text: I made a detour to get Aussie Pie and some Pav this place reminders me that I am at home when you are Australian born you will travel miles to get a good aussie pie the staff are great you can also takeaway
